		                      <div id="content-header">
                                      <h1 class="title">Call for Submissions: Blogging Textbook</h1>
                                                                                        </div> <!-- /#content-header -->
                            
<div class="node node-first node-type-blog">
  <div class="node-inner clear-block">
    <span class="date">15 Nov</span>
            	  <span class="submitted">Posted by <a href="/user/706" title="View user profile.">barclay</a></span>
              <span class="terms"> in <a href="/taxonomy/term/101" title="">blogging</a>, <a href="/taxonomy/term/158" title="">blogs</a>, <a href="/taxonomy/term/419" title="">k-log</a>, <a href="/taxonomy/term/420" title="">k-logs</a>, <a href="/taxonomy/term/121" title="">podcast</a>, <a href="/taxonomy/term/306" title="">podcasts</a>, <a href="/taxonomy/term/304" title="">textbooks</a>, <a href="/taxonomy/term/418" title="">wiki</a>, <a href="/taxonomy/term/69" title="Wikis">wikis</a></span>
        <div class="content clear-block">
      <p>I am looking for submissions to be included in an edited collection of pedagogical materials on blogging to be published by Allyn &amp; Bacon/Longman (ABL) in 2007 and to be distributed for *free* to interested instructors.  In an unprecedented move, ABL will release this text under a Creative Commons license; that&#39;s right, folks, a major textbook publisher has agreed to test the Creative Commons waters.</p>
<p>I&#39;m looking for practical handouts, activities, and assignments--things you probably already have on your hard drive (or USB flash drive) if you&#39;ve taught classes or given workshops on blogging.  All varieties of materials are invited.  Deadline for submissions is December 15, 2006.  I am inclduing the tentative Table of Contents for this project (working title (only): _Project Blogue_) below but submissions that fall outside the projected ToC are invited as well.</p>
<p>Email submissions and questions to <a href="mailto:blogs@barclaybarrios.com">blogs@barclaybarrios.com</a>.</p>
<p>Thanks,<br />Barclay</p>
<p>Barclay Barrios<br />Director of Writing Programs<br />Assistant Professor of English<br />Florida Atlantic University<br />Boca Raton, FL</p>
<p>Tentative ToC for Project Blogue</p>
<p>1.	Introduction</p>
<p>2.	Whatsa?<br />
a.	Whatsa Blog?<br />
b.	Whatsa K-log?<br />
c.	Whatsa Wiki?<br />
d.	Whatsa Podcast?<br />
e.	Assignments</p>
<p>3.	Writing<br />
a.	Different reasons for different tools<br />
b.	Popular blogging tools<br />
c.	Tutorials<br />
d.	Assignments</p>
<p>4.	Reading<br />
a.	Finding blogs<br />
b.	Noteworthy blogs<br />
c.	Tools for reading blogs<br />
d.	Assignments</p>
<p>5.	Research<br />
a.	Blogs for research<br />
b.	Researching blogs<br />
c.	Blog bibliography<br />
d.	Assignments</p>
<p>6.	Assessing</p>
<p>7.	Final Words: Pros and Cons, Dos and Don’ts</p>
    </div>
          <div class="extra-links">
        <ul class="links inline"><li class="blog_usernames_blog first"><a href="/blog/706" title="Read barclay&#039;s latest blog entries.">barclay&#039;s blog</a></li> 
